      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "This pattern, where the leaves turn pale yellow while the veins remain green, is often a sign of nutrient deficiencies, and nitrogen is a common culprit. However, soil pH issues can also cause nutrient lockup, making it hard for your bushes to absorb whatever is present. To get a clearer picture, it's best to test your soil to determine both the pH and nutrient levels. This will help you figure out if you need a nitrogen boost or a pH adjuster.",
